Key Match Events: Pringle and Van Beek take three wickets each
O'Dowd is dropped, but survives to move to 41
Max O'Dowd strikes the first boundary since the sixth over!
Post-Match Reflections: Dutch spinner Tim Pringle: 'We spoke about getting stumps in play and then hopefully the surface would do the rest for us. It was good.'

Ryan ten Doeschate, Former Netherlands all-rounder on BBC Sounds: 'The Dutch always managed the chase well. Bohara has gone away from his gameplan there, and Nepal will rue the chances they put down. It's all part of the learning for them.'
Miscellaneous Highlights: Today's match meant a lot to the people of Nepal, who packed into venues to watch it on the big screen.
Netherlands are playing South Africa at 15:30 BST on Saturday at the stadium in New York.
Nepal will be staying in the United States for their next match, travelling to Florida to face Sri Lanka next Tuesday (00:30 BST Wednesday).
